<i>Next into the tank is</i>
<i>Lyle schuette</i>

00:21:43,604 --> 00:21:46,406
<i>with a household product</i>
<i>he invented for his wife.</i>

00:21:56,617 --> 00:21:59,953
Hi. My name is Lyle schuette,
and I'm from Derby, kansas,

00:22:00,020 --> 00:22:02,623
and my product
is the heat helper.

00:22:02,689 --> 00:22:05,392
I am here today
to ask for $100,000

00:22:05,459 --> 00:22:08,629
in exchange for 50% equity
in my product.

00:22:08,695 --> 00:22:11,899
The heat helper is
an amazingly simple device.

00:22:11,965 --> 00:22:14,368
It saves energy and money,
especially in times

00:22:14,434 --> 00:22:16,370
when we need it now,
when the economy is tough.

00:22:16,436 --> 00:22:18,405
I came up
with the heat helper

00:22:18,472 --> 00:22:20,073
out of pure necessity.
(chuckles)

00:22:20,140 --> 00:22:22,976
My wife had injured her back
and during her recovery

00:22:23,043 --> 00:22:26,313
asked if there was any way that
I could raise the Dryer up

00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:28,415
so when she did laundry
she wouldn't have to bend over

00:22:28,482 --> 00:22:29,816
to get the clothes
in and out of the Dryer,

00:22:29,883 --> 00:22:31,418
"and while you're at it,

00:22:31,485 --> 00:22:32,920
can you heat up
that end of the house?"

00:22:32,986 --> 00:22:35,989
now my mother--
she was a very smart woman.

00:22:36,056 --> 00:22:36,990
Now I remember back home

00:22:37,057 --> 00:22:39,092
on my parents' dairy farm
in wisconsin,

00:22:39,159 --> 00:22:41,428
my mother would take
her old panty hose

00:22:41,495 --> 00:22:43,230
and stick on the back
of the Dryer.

00:22:43,297 --> 00:22:45,999
Why? Because she could catch
the heat and the humidity

00:22:46,066 --> 00:22:48,635
that came out of the Dryer,
so during laundry day,

00:22:48,702 --> 00:22:50,637
our home was
a lot more comfortable.

00:22:50,704 --> 00:22:52,573
Now before I explain
how the heat helper works,

00:22:52,639 --> 00:22:55,676
you must first understand
how an ELECTRIC Dryer Works.

00:22:55,742 --> 00:22:58,679
An electric Dryer works
by pulling in air

00:22:58,745 --> 00:23:00,547
through the back of the unit,
heating that air up.

00:23:00,614 --> 00:23:02,816
Then it blows the air out
of your home.

00:23:02,883 --> 00:23:04,418
What a waste.

00:23:04,484 --> 00:23:06,920
Now what the heat helper does
is take that same amount of Air

00:23:06,987 --> 00:23:09,990
that your Dryer uses,
filters it,

00:23:10,057 --> 00:23:12,492
and then blowing it
back inside your home.

00:23:12,559 --> 00:23:15,462
It pays for itself
in the first year.

00:23:15,529 --> 00:23:16,797
I call the Heat helper...

00:23:16,864 --> 00:23:18,999
(taps)
Common sense in a box.

00:23:19,066 --> 00:23:21,902
(Robert chuckles)
Now Let's do some Business.

00:23:21,969 --> 00:23:23,270
(mark, daymond,
and Robert laugh)

00:23:23,337 --> 00:23:27,374
first question I have to ask is,
if my wife hurt her back

00:23:27,441 --> 00:23:30,644
and I didn't volunteer to do
the laundry for her...

00:23:30,711 --> 00:23:31,812
(Barbara laughs)
I'd be black and blue.

00:23:31,879 --> 00:23:32,813
How did you get away
with that?

00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:35,415
Well, I started
a dirt business,

00:23:35,482 --> 00:23:37,751
and I'm normally gone
all day long,

00:23:37,818 --> 00:23:40,053
and since my wife, at that time,
was a stay-at-home mom,

00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:41,221
it was all right for her
to do that.
She--she cut you

00:23:41,288 --> 00:23:42,422
